<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Cleaning and Inspection - Checking Camshaft Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="0">
        <title>Checking Camshaft Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bristle brush and a suitable solvent to clean the camshaft and cam gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the cam gear for worn and damaged teeth. Replace the gear assembly, if necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the camshaft for scuffed, scored and cracked lobes. Replace the camshaft if
                necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the camshaft thrust plate for wear, cracks, and distortion. Use an outside
                micrometer to measure the thickness of the thrust plate. If the thrust plate is too worn or damaged,
                replace the thrust plate.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
